[{"id":"VR733066","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR733052.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">In context, which of the following best identifies the metaphorical meaning of “Ornament” (line 20) ?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR733066_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">\n<p class=\"introduction passage-intro\"><span class=\"formatted_text font_weight:bold\">Read the following poem carefully before you choose your answers.</span></p>\n\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<p class=\"passage_para\"><span class=\"formatted_text font_style:italic\">Katherine Philips’s poem “Friendship’s Mystery, To my Dearest Lucasia” was published in 1655.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"poetry style:1\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<p class=\"title_line passage-title\">Friendship’s Mystery, To my Dearest Lucasia</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Come, my <span class=\"formatted_text font_style:italic\">Lucasia</span>, since we see</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>That Miracles Mens faith do move,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>By wonder and by prodigy</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>To the dull angry<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">1</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">vexing, annoying</span></span> world let’s prove</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">5&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>There’s a Religion in our Love.</span></div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>For though we were design’d t’agree,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>That Fate no liberty destroyes,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>But our Election<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">2</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">exercise of choice</span></span> is as free</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>As Angels, who with greedy<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">3</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">eager</span></span> choice</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">10&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>Are yet determin’d to their joyes.</span></div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Our hearts are doubled by the loss,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>Here Mixture is Addition grown;</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>We both diffuse, and both ingross:<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">4</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">absorb</span></span></span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>And we whose minds are so much one,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">15&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>Never, yet ever are alone.</span></div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>We court our own Captivity</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>Than Thrones<span class=\"footnote\" tabindex=\"0\"><span class=\"footnote_mark\">5</span><span class=\"footnote_text\">name of a category of angels</span></span> more great and innocent:</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>’Twere banishment to be set free,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>Since we wear fetters whose intent</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">20&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>Not Bondage is, but Ornament.</span></div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Divided joyes are tedious found,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>And griefs united easier grow:</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>We are our selves but by rebound,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>And all our Titles shuffled so,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">25&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>Both Princes, and both Subjects too.</span></div>\n\n<div class=\"verse\"><span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Our Hearts are mutual Victims laid,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>While they (such power in Friendship lies)</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_0\"></span>Are Altars, Priests, and Off’rings made:</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>And each Heart which thus kindly dies,</span><br />\n<span class=\"line\"><span class=\"line_number badge badge-inverse\">30&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span class=\"indent indent_2\"></span>Grows deathless by the Sacrifice.</span></div>\n<span class=\"mandatory_credit_line\"></span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Approval by society</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Trust in religion</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Harmony in relationships</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Enrichment in friendship</p>"],"answer":4}]